Our company is looking for an Sr. Software Engineer/ Data Engineer/Big Data Analyst who will be performing following roles and responsibilities: Serve as a technical liaison effectively working with large data and configuration of different tools/frameworks/products/ applications to meet specific project implementation objectives. Design, development, customization, integration and implementation of the software products Big Data, Data Analytics and Visualization solutions. Design and Develop Big Data Management framework. Build Data warehouse/Data Marts. Build data platforms utilizing Spark distributed computing. Implement ETL processes. Monitor performance and advising any necessary infrastructure changes. Develop processes and scripts for Big Data utilizing Hadoop, HBase, Hive, Pig, and HBase, HiveQL. Design and implement solutions using Hadoop related technologies such as SPARK, HDFS and IMPALA. Code high-performance code in SCALA/ PYTHON and Machine Learning. Develop dashboards using tools such as Tableau, SQLBI/Power BI and MySQL. Develop comprehensive analytical solutions, dashboards, forecasts, trend analysis, A/B testing of product suit Deploy products in SaaS model on AWS Cloud or Azure Cloud. Minimum Requirements Bachelor’s Degree in Computer Science/ Information Technology or closely related field. 40 hr wk. M-F. Please mail the resume at Alpha Clinical Systems, Inc. JOB# 2_0321, 15 Corporate Place South, Suite#420, Piscataway, NJ 08854.
